Whereas the Government of Venezuela’s chronic mismanagement of its economy has produced inflation
			 that exceeds 50 percent annually, currency shortages, economic
			 distortions, and the routine absence of  basic goods and foodstuffs;

Whereas, on January 23, 2014, National Representative Maria Corina Machado and Mr. Leopoldo López,
			 leader of the political party Popular Will, among others, called on the Venezuelan people to gather in street assemblies and debate a
			 popular, democratic and constitutional way out of Venezuela’s crisis of governability;

Whereas the Maduro government has sought to censor information about the demonstrations and the
			 government’s violent crackdown by blocking online images and threatening
			 the few remaining uncensored domestic media outlets;

